            <p class="hca-typography--subhead hca-typography__color--asphalt">Tabs are a common and easy way to switch between related views or content.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">They can be utilized as app-level navigation that switches between entire views, or content-level navigation that changes content or data sets within a single view.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Tabs should always be presented in a single row.</p>
            <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Since swipe gestures can be used to navigate tabs, avoid pairing swipable content with tabbed navigation.</p>
